cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.HC 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with visual kin-based problems and the authors use convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for feature extraction. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is also likely as the dataset involves collecting and labelling a large set of family images. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the authors compare the performance of different feature types and machine vision algorithms. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is a possible category as the paper involves searching and retrieving images based on kinship relationships. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is also a possible category as the authors measure human performance and discuss the design of their labelling tool.
